<DOC><DOCNO> AP880601-0073 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-01-88 0604EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Bangladesh-Storm     06-01 0184</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Bangladesh-Storm,0190</SECOND><HEAD>Six Killed In Hurricane</HEAD><DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A hurricane swept across parts ofBangladesh for two days this week, killing at least six people,injuring hundreds more and destroying thousands of homes, officialsand news reports said today.   A government official at Gaibandha, 124 miles north of Dhaka,said three people were killed and 170 injured when the storm hitthe area on Monday and Tuesday.   The official, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said at least1,500 houses, mostly made of mud and straw, were blown away. Cropsover a wide area were damaged.   Newspapers said at least three other people were killed in otherparts of the country. Hundreds of others were reported injured, theBangladesh Times newspaper said.   The storm followed floods in northern areas of the country,caused by the Brahmaputra river bursting its banks.   The government says at least 13 people have been killed in thefloods but local newspapers put the figure at more than 50.   Floods and heavy rain are common in Bangladesh at this time ofyear, when the annual monsoon begins.</TEXT></DOC>